title: Maker Studios Axes PewDiePie for Anti-Semitic Videos | Variety
text:
Courtesy of PewDiePie/Maker Studios February 13, 2017 | 06:06PM PT 
Disney has dropped YouTube star PewDiePie from its Maker Studios online video venture after videos with anti-semitic jokes surfaced online. 
PewDiePie is the pseudonym of Felix Kjellberg, a Swedish online video star that has amassed close to 14.7 billion video views on his main channel alone. 
Disneyâ€™s decision to sever ties with Kjellberg were first reported by the Wall Street Journal late Monday.
